British number one Heather Watson resisted the challenge of Jovana Jaksic to reach the second round of the Japan Women's Open.

The 22-year-old, who won the top prize in Osaka two years ago, recovered from losing the opening set to her Serbian opponent to triumph 3-6, 6-4, 6-2 at the Utsubo Tennis Center.

Watson will face Russian teenager Yulia Putintseva in the next round.

